Phenomenography
---------------

Phenomenography is a method of discovery (rather than hypothesis testing)
that produces qualitative data about categories of experience.
In teaching, phenomenography shows us:

 1.  how students' and teachers' conceptions of the subject matter differ,
     and how we might make those conceptions explicit,
     so they may be usefully compared and contrasted
 2.  the characteristics of successful and unsuccessful
     student--teacher--subject matter interactions

